        <h2 MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">How to Use Local Formatting to Set Rounded Borders on Block Elements</h2>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Paragraphs-Modify-First-Steps.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only" />
        <ol MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">
            <li value="3">
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Do-One-Following-Depending-UI.flsnp" />
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Ribbon </span>Select <b>Home &gt; <img src="../../../Images/Shared/Co-D2-Fl/Interface/Buttons/Arrow-btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /></b> (at the bottom of the <span class="Emphasis">Paragraph</span> section). </p>
                    </li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Keyboard Shortcut</span> Press <span class="Emphasis">CTRL+ALT+B</span>. </li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Right-Click </span>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Right-Click-Paragraph-Properties.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>The Paragraph Properties dialog opens.</p>
            </li>
            <li>Select the <span class="Emphasis">Borders</span> tab.</li>
            <li>
                <p>Set the options in the <span class="Emphasis">Border Radius</span> section.</p>
                <ol class="LowerAlpha">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders1.flsnp" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/General/Formatting-Borders2.flsnp" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders3.flsnp" />
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders2.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders4.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders5.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Click-OK.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li>In the Paragraph Properties dialog, click <span class="Emphasis">OK</span>.</li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Save-File.flsnp" />
            </li>
        </ol>
        <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="Flare-Guides.Flare-Tables-Guide" />
        <h2>How to Use a Table Stylesheet to Set Rounded Borders on Tables</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Open the table stylesheet that you want to edit. This can be found in the <span class="Emphasis">Resources &gt; TableStyles</span> subfolder in the Content Explorer, but you can store table stylesheets in other folders in the Content Explorer if you like.</li>
            <li>In the Table Style Editor, select the <span class="Emphasis">General</span> tab.</li>
            <li>In the <span class="Emphasis">Cell Border Collapse</span> area, select <span class="Emphasis">Do not collapse cell borders</span>.</li>
            <li>
                <p>Set the options in the <span class="Emphasis">Border Radius</span> section.</p>
                <ol class="LowerAlpha">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders-Tables1.flsnp" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/General/Formatting-Borders2.flsnp" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders3.flsnp" />
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders2.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders4.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/Co-Fl/Paragraphs/Formatting-Rounded-Borders5.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Click-OK.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li>Scroll down to the bottom of the tab, and in the <span class="Emphasis">Advanced</span> area, click in the <span class="Emphasis">Overflow</span> drop-down and select <span class="Emphasis">Hidden</span>.</li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Save-File.flsnp" />
            </li>
        </ol>
        <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="Flare-Guides.Flare-Tables-Guide" />
        <h2 MadCap:conditions="General.Print-Only">How to Use a Regular Stylesheet to Set Rounded Borders on Tables</h2>
        <ol MadCap:conditions="General.Print-Only">
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../Styles/Edit-Style1.flsnp" />
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
